The Evolution of Alternatives
The Alternative for Germany party was formed in September 2012 on the basis of the group "Alternative Choice 2013" which included people from the Christian Democratic Union.
The group initially opposed the government's course, but at first focused only on economic issues, including the euro and EU engagement.
At the same time, the group opposed Germany's "sponsorship" of weak EU economies, did not rule out the possibility of a return to the German brand and the complete withdrawal of the country from the European Union.
Amid the deepening immigration crisis, the ADG's political platform has expanded.
In 2013, the group became a full-fledged party that occupied a niche of Eurosceptics and began to harshly criticize the government for the failure of immigration policy.
In the last parliamentary elections in 2017, the AGG managed to break into the Bundestag for the first time, winning 94 seats (out of 709).
